              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A constant specifying the color picking mode. These constants are defined in "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "AppKit/NSColorPanel.h"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "In grayscale-alpha, red-green-blue, cyan-magenta-yellow-black, and hue-saturation-brightness modes, the user adjusts colors by manipulating sliders. In the custom palette mode, the user can load an "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSImage"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " file (TIFF or EPS) into the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSColorPanel"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", then select colors from the image. In custom color list mode, the user can create and load lists of named colors. The two custom modes provide "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSPopUpList"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "s for loading and saving files. Finally, color wheel mode provides a simplified control for selecting colors."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
